<exercise checkit-seed="0028" checkit-slug="V9" checkit-title="Homogeneous systems">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the homogeneous system of equations 
    <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 5 "><mrow>x_{1} &amp;-&amp; x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 6 \, x_{3} &amp;+&amp; 9 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow><mrow>2 \, x_{1} &amp;-&amp; x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 8 \, x_{3} &amp;+&amp; 11 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow><mrow> &amp; &amp; 2 \, x_{2} &amp;-&amp; 7 \, x_{3} &amp;-&amp; 12 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow><mrow>x_{1} &amp; &amp;  &amp;+&amp; 6 \, x_{3} &amp;+&amp; 10 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow></md></p>
    <ol>
      <li> Find the solution space of this system.</li>
      <li> Find a basis of the solution space.</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>
      <me>\operatorname{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccc|c}
1 &amp; -1 &amp; 6 &amp; 9 &amp; 0 \\
2 &amp; -1 &amp; 8 &amp; 11 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 2 &amp; -7 &amp; -12 &amp; 0 \\
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 6 &amp; 10 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccc|c}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>The solution space is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \, a \\
-a \\
-2 \, a \\
a
\end{array}\right] \middle|\,a\in\mathbb{R}\right\} </m></li>
      <li>A basis of the solution space is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
-1 \\
-2 \\
1
\end{array}\right] \right\} </m>.</li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

